As pointed out on github by [chiochuan][1], the workaround is to add

       discriminator: &quot;type&quot;

to the parent&#39;s definition to make the Java child classes extend it.

    definitions:
      Pet:
        type: &quot;object&quot;
        discriminator: &quot;type&quot;
        required:
          - &quot;name&quot;
        properties:
          name:
            type: &quot;string&quot;
            example: &quot;doggie&quot;

It&#39;s a bit strange as the OpenAPI Specification Version 2.0 state that the [`discriminator` Fixed Field][2] must reference a property from the same schema, and that it must be a `required` property, both of which isn&#39;t the case - but it works, at least as of today. :)


